flowRoot.flowPara: The Automatic Report Compilation Tool (ARCTool) is only the bleeding edge in automagic document generation. No one should have to summarise months of emails while there's real work needing doing. ARCTool does all the leg work and spits out an organised, editable document. Just put your name at the top. Through the use of powerful plugins, ARCTool can read emails, browse websites and make bulleted lists, all at the click of a button!

flowRoot.flowPara: These two pages are a reduction of thirteen pages of emails. Although some editing for content is still required, the majority of email fluff has been removed.
ARCTool's source code is available at
The profile toolbar allows you to edit the name of the report and set a context.
The section list allows you to create, remove and rearange sections of the report.
The section tools are used to name the section and assign a plugin.
Each plugin has its own collection of widgets used to configure the plugin to the report.
Once the profile is complete, the report can be generated and exported to various file formats.
ARCTool uses Python 3 and PyQt5. This means that ARCTool is both easy to develop for and cross-platform! Plugins can be incredibly powerful by using Python toolkits like NLTK or TensorFlow.
